27 400.9992 Legislative findings and intent.—The Legislature
28 finds that unregulated facilities providing care to patients
29 recovering from surgical or medical procedures present risks to
30 patient safety, health, and well-being. It is the intent of the
31 Legislature to establish clear standards, licensing
32 requirements, and oversight for such facilities to ensure the
33 safe recovery of patients and to prevent confusion with
34 addiction recovery residences.
35 Section 4. Section 400.9993, Florida Statutes, is created
36 to read:
37 400.9993 Definitions.—As used in this part, the term:
38 (1) "Agency" means the Agency for Health Care
39 Administration.
40 (2) "Patient" means an individual admitted to a
41 postsurgical recovery home following a medical or surgical
42 procedure.
43 (3) "Postsurgical recovery home" means a licensed
44 residential facility providing short-term, nonacute care and
45 support to patients recovering from surgical or medical
46 procedures, that is staffed with licensed healthcare
47 professionals.
48 (4) "Recovery plan" means a written care plan developed in
49 coordination with the patient's surgeon or medical provider
50 outlining necessary postoperative care.
