51 Section 5. Section 400.9994, Florida Statutes, is created
52 to read:
53 400.9994 Licensure.—
54 (1) A person or an entity must be licensed by the agency
55 to operate a postsurgical recovery home.
56 (2) An applicant for licensure must submit all of the
57 following:
58 (a) Proof of compliance with all facility safety
59 standards.
60 (b) Criminal background checks for all owners and staff.
61 (c) Proof of general liability and medical malpractice
62 insurance.
63 (3) The agency shall inspect each postsurgical recovery
64 home before issuing a license and annually thereafter.
65 Section 6. Section 400.9995, Florida Statutes, is created
66 to read:
67 400.9995 Minimum standards for postsurgical recovery
68 homes.—
69 (1)(a) At least one licensed practical nurse or registered
70 nurse must be onsite or on-call 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.
71 (b) All staff must be trained in cardiopulmonary
72 resuscitation, basic wound care, and postoperative care
73 procedures.
74 (2) The ratio of staff-to-patients must be maintained as
75 follows:
